<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB09008</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT MAKING THE STATE UNIVERSITIES AND COLLEGES SPECIAL EDUCATION (SPED)-FRIENDLY</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Intends to reinforce the State's policies as stated in Section 2 of Republic Act No. 7277,
otherwise known as the Magna Carta for Disabled Persons.

Proposes an enabling environment for students with physical and mental disabilities
by: improving the quality and accessibility of SUC facilities; creating a curriculum responsive
to their specific needs; and ensuring SUCs as a community for these students to be able to enjoy academic freedom and uphold their right to education.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ELAGO, SARAH JANE I.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-01-31</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HIGHER AND TECHNICAL EDUCATION ON 2019-02-04</td></tr></table>